<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-03-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-03-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="592" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d592">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">810.79611 Pan American Airways,
                                Inc./56</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Geissler</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-03-26"><hi rend="italic">March 26,
                                        1928</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received April 4.]</dateline>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 1861</seg></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to the Department’s
                                cablegram No. 26 [<hi rend="italic">21</hi>] of March 16, 5 p.m.
                                instructing the Legation to render all possible and <pb facs="0907" n="779" xml:id="pg_779"/> proper assistance to Mr. John D.
                                MacGregor, Vice President of the Pan American Airways Incorporated,
                                in his effort to obtain a transport concession, I have the honor to
                                report, that I arranged for the President of Guatemala to receive
                                Mr. MacGregor today, and that since then he has informed me, that he
                                has had a very pleasant preliminary talk with President Chacón
                                concerning his project, and that he will visit the Minister of the
                                Interior (<hi rend="italic">Fomento</hi>) tomorrow, as suggested by
                                the President, for the purpose of discussing details.</p>
                            <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Arthur H.
                                Geissler</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>